1. CIA (Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability)
Opposite of CIA is DAD (Disclosure, Alteration, Destruction)

Disclosure: Someone not authorized getting access to your Resources/information.
Alteration: Your data has been changed.
Destruction: Your system / Data has been destroyed or rendered inaccessible.

2. IAAA (Identification, Authentication, Authorization and Accountability)
Identification: Your name
Authentication: Should be always done MFA
    Something You Know: Password, Pass Phrase, PIN ETC.
    Something You Have: ID, Passport, Smart Card, Token, Cookie on PC 
    Something You Are: Fingerprint, Biometric, IRIS scan, Facial Geometry. 


